3 May 2021 The Government Communication and Information System and the Department of Justice and Constitutional Development will host a virtual panel discussion on the rights of LGBTQI+ community. Members of the media are invited to attend and cover the panel discussion. Details are as follows: Date: Wednesday, 05 May 2021 - postponed until further noticeTime: 10h00 – 11h00Platform: Zoom (ID 933 8169 8478; Passcode: 088734)https://gcis.zoom.us/j/93381698478?pwd=UmpiNmFacGtvT2pjc2RRYmQ0YjIxQT09 The panel discussion will also be live-streamed on the following social media links below: Facebook: http://facebook.com/GovernmentZA Twitter: http://twitter.com/GCISMedia YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/user/GovernmentZA RSVP to Ignicious Masilela on Email: Ignicious@gcis.gov.za Enquiries:William BaloyiCell: 083 390 7147 Issued by Government Communications